VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT new\s*HttpGet|new\s*HttpPost|new\s*HttpPut|new\s*HttpDelete|new\s*HttpURLConnection
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:http:// && MISSING:https://
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects the usage of HTTP client classes (HttpGet, HttpPost, HttpPut, HttpDelete, HttpURLConnection) without encryption, potentially resulting in information leaks.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Unencrypted Data Transmission over HTTP.
